\mt2 The Epistle of Paul to the  
\mt1 PHILIPPIANS  
\c 1  
\s1 Salutation  
\m
\v 1 \w Paul|strong="G3972"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w Timothy|strong="G5095"\w*,\f + \fr 1:1 \ft Paul gives recognition to his junior partner.\f* \w slaves|strong="G1401"\w*\f + \fr 1:1 \ft That is right, slaves.\f* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*, \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* saints \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*\f + \fr 1:1 \ft Paul goes back and forth between “Jesus Christ” and “Christ Jesus” with apparently no difference in meaning.\f* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w at|strong="G1722"\w* \w Philippi|strong="G5375"\w*, \w together|strong="G4862"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w overseers|strong="G1985"\w*\f + \fr 1:1 \ft This term is often translated ‘bishop’; along with ‘elder’ and ‘pastor’ it refers to a single office in the church. Note that there is a plurality of both overseers and deacons.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w deacons|strong="G1249"\w*:  
\v 2 \w Grace|strong="G5485"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w peace|strong="G1515"\w* \w from|strong="G1515"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* Sovereign \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*.   
\s1 How Paul prays for them  
\p
\v 3 \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w thank|strong="G2168"\w* \w my|strong="G3956"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w time|strong="G1909"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* remember \w you|strong="G5210"\w*;  
\v 4 \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w prayers|strong="G1162"\w* \w for|strong="G5228"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w of|strong="G1722"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w always|strong="G3842"\w* \w pray|strong="G1162"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w joy|strong="G5479"\w*,  
\v 5 \w because|strong="G1909"\w* \w of|strong="G2250"\w* \w your|strong="G1909"\w* partnership \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w Gospel|strong="G2098"\w* \w from|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w first|strong="G4413"\w* \w day|strong="G2250"\w* \w until|strong="G1519"\w* \w now|strong="G3568"\w*,  
\v 6 \w being|strong="G5547"\w* certain \w of|strong="G2250"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w very|strong="G3778"\w* \w thing|strong="G3778"\w*, \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w He|strong="G3754"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w began|strong="G1728"\w* \w a|strong="G1722"\w* \w good|strong="G3588"\w* \w work|strong="G2041"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w will|strong="G2250"\w* \w complete|strong="G2005"\w* \w it|strong="G3754"\w* \w until|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Day|strong="G2250"\w* \w of|strong="G2250"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*;\f + \fr 1:6 \ft Amen!\f*  
\v 7 \w just|strong="G2531"\w* \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w right|strong="G1342"\w* \w for|strong="G5228"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w think|strong="G5426"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w*, \w because|strong="G1223"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w heart|strong="G2588"\w*, inasmuch \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w both|strong="G2532"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w chains|strong="G1199"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* defense \w and|strong="G2532"\w* confirmation \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Gospel|strong="G2098"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w partakers|strong="G4791"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Grace|strong="G5485"\w*.\f + \fr 1:7 \ft That is what the Text says, ‘the’ grace. They identified with Paul and what he was doing.\f*  
\v 8 \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w witness|strong="G3144"\w* \w how|strong="G5613"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w long|strong="G1971"\w* \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w affection|strong="G4698"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*.   
\p
\v 9 \w This|strong="G3778"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w what|strong="G3588"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w pray|strong="G4336"\w*: \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* love \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w abound|strong="G4052"\w* \w yet|strong="G2089"\w* \w more|strong="G3123"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w more|strong="G3123"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w real|strong="G1922"\w* \w knowledge|strong="G1922"\w*\f + \fr 1:9 \ft The compound noun, επιγνωσις, is often rendered as ‘full knowledge’, but I consider that ‘real knowledge’ comes closer.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w full|strong="G3956"\w* discernment,\f + \fr 1:9 \ft We have all heard that ‘love is blind’, but \+it agape\+it* love is just the opposite. Lamentably, I cannot think of a single church that could be said to have “full discernment”, and many appear to have none at all.\f*  
\v 10 \w for|strong="G1519"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* identify \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* really \w matter|strong="G1308"\w*;\f + \fr 1:10 \ft Yes indeed, “the things that really matter”—the point of identifying them is to concentrate our attention and energy on them.\f* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w sincere|strong="G1506"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* blameless \w until|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Day|strong="G2250"\w* \w of|strong="G2250"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*,\f + \fr 1:10 \ft In verse 6 the emphasis is on God's sovereignty, here it is on our responsibility. “The Day of Christ” is of special relevance to Christians, and the particular aspect in view here is the accounting (see Romans 14:12,14).\f*  
\v 11 \w having|strong="G2532"\w* \w been|strong="G2532"\w* \w filled|strong="G4137"\w*\f + \fr 1:11 \ft “Having been filled”—that is what the Text says. Since the righteousness of Christ is imputed (we cannot earn it), God gives us the best possible start; as it says in 2 Peter 1:3, “His divine power has given us all things that pertain to life and godliness”. What we do with it is up to us (see 2:12 below).\f* \w with|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w fruits|strong="G2590"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w righteousness|strong="G1343"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*, \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w glory|strong="G1391"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w praise|strong="G1868"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*.\f + \fr 1:11 \ft The glory of God is the ultimate purpose of all creation (Isaiah 43:7).\f*   
\ms1 News and Instructions  
\s1 By whatever means, Christ is preached  
\p
\v 12 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w want|strong="G1014"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w know|strong="G1097"\w*, brothers, \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* events \w against|strong="G2596"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G1473"\w* actually \w turned|strong="G2064"\w* \w out|strong="G2064"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* advancement \w of|strong="G2098"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w Gospel|strong="G2098"\w*:  
\v 13 \w as|strong="G1722"\w* \w a|strong="G1096"\w* \w result|strong="G5620"\w*, \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w has|strong="G1096"\w* \w become|strong="G1096"\w* \w evident|strong="G5318"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w whole|strong="G3650"\w* imperial \w guard|strong="G2532"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w everyone|strong="G3956"\w* \w else|strong="G3062"\w*, \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1473"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w chains|strong="G1199"\w* \w for|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*;\f + \fr 1:13 \ft Paul did not hide his light ‘under a bushel’.\f*  
\v 14 \w also|strong="G2532"\w*, \w most|strong="G4183"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* brothers \w in|strong="G1722"\w* Sovereign \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w been|strong="G2532"\w* influenced \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w chains|strong="G1199"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w much|strong="G4183"\w* bolder, \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w speak|strong="G2980"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Word|strong="G3056"\w* fearlessly.  
\v 15 \w To|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w sure|strong="G3303"\w*, \w some|strong="G5100"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w even|strong="G2532"\w* \w preaching|strong="G2784"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w out|strong="G2532"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w envy|strong="G5355"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w rivalry|strong="G2054"\w*, \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w others|strong="G3588"\w* \w out|strong="G2532"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w good|strong="G2107"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w*;  
\v 16 \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w former|strong="G3588"\w* proclaim Christ \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* selfish ambition, not sincerely, thinking \w to|strong="G1519"\w* add \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w my|strong="G3754"\w* affliction \w while|strong="G3754"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* chains,\f + \fr 1:16 \ft Just a minute: how does insincere preaching (by others) add to his affliction? I suppose we all know ‘Christian workers’ who are motivated by selfish ambition, and any such would want to ‘make hay’ while free from Paul's ‘shadow’, as it were. Judging Paul by themselves, they would think he would be bothered by seeing them gaining prominence at his expense.\f*  
\v 17 \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* latter \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* love, knowing \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1473"\w* set here \w for|strong="G1161"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* defense \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* Gospel.\f + \fr 1:17 \ft Even in prison Paul did not lose sight of the job God had given him. Some 10% of the Greek manuscripts transpose verses 16 and 17 (as in NIV, NASB, LB, TEV, etc.).\f*  
\v 18 \w No|strong="G2532"\w* problem: \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w way|strong="G5158"\w*, \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w pretense|strong="G4392"\w* \w or|strong="G1535"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* truth,\f + \fr 1:18 \ft The Bible is clear to the effect that the means, not just the end, must be appropriate to God's character, so this statement seems a bit strange. Within the community of faith deviations can be treated quite severely, but perhaps for what we might term ‘pre-evangelism’, getting people who have never heard of Him before to start thinking about Christ, there may be some leeway. Further, Matthew 20:1-16 makes clear that God is prepared to use a variety of types of worker.\f* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w is|strong="G5101"\w* \w proclaimed|strong="G2605"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w rejoice|strong="G5463"\w*—\w yes|strong="G1063"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G5101"\w* \w rejoice|strong="G5463"\w*.   
\s1 To live is Christ, to die is gain  
\p
\v 19 \w You|strong="G5210"\w* \w see|strong="G1492"\w*, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* turn \w out|strong="G2532"\w* \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w deliverance|strong="G4991"\w* (\w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w your|strong="G1223"\w* \w supplication|strong="G1162"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* support \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*)\f + \fr 1:19 \ft This is presumably a reference to the Holy Spirit (see John 16:13-15).\f*  
\v 20 \w according|strong="G2596"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* earnest expectation \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w hope|strong="G1680"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3762"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w put|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* shame \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w anything|strong="G3762"\w* \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w truly|strong="G1722"\w* \w bold|strong="G3954"\w*, \w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w now|strong="G3568"\w* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w always|strong="G3842"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w glorified|strong="G2532"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* person, \w whether|strong="G1535"\w* \w by|strong="G1223"\w* \w life|strong="G2222"\w* \w or|strong="G1535"\w* \w by|strong="G1223"\w* \w death|strong="G2288"\w*\f + \fr 1:20 \ft Although it appears that Paul actually hoped to be freed from prison, he is prepared to die. His main concern is not to do anything that will shame his Master.\f*  
\v 21 —\w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w live|strong="G2198"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* die \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w gain|strong="G2771"\w*.\f + \fr 1:21 \ft How can death be a gain? Only if you live for Christ.\f*  
\v 22 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1473"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w live|strong="G2198"\w* \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w flesh|strong="G4561"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G5101"\w* \w mean|strong="G5101"\w* \w fruitful|strong="G2590"\w* \w labor|strong="G2041"\w* \w for|strong="G1161"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w do|strong="G5101"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w know|strong="G1722"\w* \w what|strong="G5101"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* choose.  
\v 23 \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* torn \w between|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w two|strong="G1417"\w*: \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w desire|strong="G1939"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* depart \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w with|strong="G4862"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* (\w far|strong="G3123"\w* \w better|strong="G2909"\w*),\f + \fr 1:23 \ft This is one of a few passages that lead us to believe that when a true believer dies his spirit goes directly to be with Christ in Heaven, not to the good side of Hades/Sheol (the ‘bosom of Abraham’) as with the Old Testament saints.\f*  
\v 24 \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w to|strong="G1722"\w* \w remain|strong="G1961"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w flesh|strong="G4561"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w more|strong="G1161"\w* necessary, \w because|strong="G1223"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*.\f + \fr 1:24 \ft His commitment to the Cause is more important than his personal desire.\f*  
\v 25 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w having|strong="G2532"\w* \w been|strong="G2532"\w* \w persuaded|strong="G3982"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w*, \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w remain|strong="G3306"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w continue|strong="G3306"\w* \w with|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w progress|strong="G4297"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w joy|strong="G5479"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w*,  
\v 26 \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w your|strong="G1223"\w* \w rejoicing|strong="G2745"\w* \w over|strong="G4052"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w may|strong="G2443"\w* \w be|strong="G2443"\w* \w more|strong="G3825"\w* \w abundant|strong="G4052"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*, \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w my|strong="G1699"\w* \w coming|strong="G3952"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w again|strong="G3825"\w*.\f + \fr 1:26 \ft Evidently Paul had a sincere hope that he would be released from prison.\f*   
\p
\v 27 \w Only|strong="G3440"\w* \w conduct|strong="G4176"\w* \w yourselves|strong="G4771"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* manner worthy \w of|strong="G4012"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Gospel|strong="G2098"\w* \w of|strong="G4012"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w whether|strong="G1535"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w come|strong="G2064"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w see|strong="G3708"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*, \w or|strong="G1535"\w* \w am|strong="G2532"\w* absent, \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* hear \w about|strong="G4012"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w stand|strong="G4739"\w* \w firm|strong="G4739"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w spirit|strong="G4151"\w*, \w striving|strong="G4866"\w* \w together|strong="G4866"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w* \w of|strong="G4012"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Gospel|strong="G2098"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w soul|strong="G5590"\w*,  
\v 28 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w being|strong="G1510"\w* intimidated \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w any|strong="G3367"\w* \w way|strong="G1722"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* opponents: \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w an|strong="G2532"\w* indicator \w of|strong="G5259"\w* ruin,\f + \fr 1:28 \ft How shall we understand this? What is the effect of our boldness in the face of opposition—do the opponents consider that we are sealing our own fate, or do they suspect that they may be on the wrong side? Perhaps both.\f* \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w of|strong="G5259"\w* \w deliverance|strong="G4991"\w*,\f + \fr 1:28 \ft Our confidence in God assures us of deliverance, one way or another: by life or by death.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w from|strong="G2532"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*.  
\v 29 \w For|strong="G3754"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w has|strong="G5547"\w* \w been|strong="G2532"\w* \w granted|strong="G5483"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w on|strong="G1519"\w* \w behalf|strong="G5228"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w only|strong="G3440"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w believe|strong="G4100"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*,\f + \fr 1:29 \ft The Text never has “believe ‘in’ Jesus”; we must believe \+nd into\+nd* Him. Being on the outside we must change location. This involves commitment and a change of worldview or value system.\f* \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w suffer|strong="G3958"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w His|strong="G1519"\w* \w sake|strong="G5228"\w*,\f + \fr 1:29 \ft If you were taught to expect a ‘bed of roses’, you had a bad teacher.\f*  
\v 30 \w having|strong="G2192"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w same|strong="G2532"\w* struggle \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G1722"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w now|strong="G3568"\w* hear \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*.\f + \fr 1:30 \ft They had seen him suffer when he first visited Philippi, and he was presently suffering in prison.\f*   
\c 2  
\s1 About having the mind of Christ  
\m
\v 1 \w Therefore|strong="G3767"\w*, \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G5547"\w* \w any|strong="G5100"\w* \w encouragement|strong="G3874"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*, \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w any|strong="G5100"\w* \w comfort|strong="G3874"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* love, \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w any|strong="G5100"\w* \w fellowship|strong="G2842"\w* \w from|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w*, \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w any|strong="G5100"\w* tenderness \w and|strong="G2532"\w* acts \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w compassion|strong="G3628"\w*,  
\v 2 \w make|strong="G4137"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w joy|strong="G5479"\w* \w full|strong="G4137"\w* \w by|strong="G1520"\w* \w being|strong="G2192"\w* like-minded, \w having|strong="G2192"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* same love, \w being|strong="G2192"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w in|strong="G2192"\w* \w spirit|strong="G4861"\w* \w and|strong="G1520"\w* \w purpose|strong="G5426"\w*.  
\v 3 \w Do|strong="G2233"\w* \w nothing|strong="G3367"\w* \w out|strong="G1438"\w* \w of|strong="G2596"\w* \w selfish|strong="G2052"\w* \w ambition|strong="G2052"\w* \w or|strong="G3366"\w* \w conceit|strong="G2754"\w*, \w but|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G2596"\w* \w humility|strong="G5012"\w* \w regard|strong="G2233"\w* \w one|strong="G3367"\w* \w another|strong="G1438"\w* \w as|strong="G2596"\w* \w being|strong="G2596"\w* \w better|strong="G5242"\w* \w than|strong="G5242"\w* \w yourselves|strong="G1438"\w*.\f + \fr 2:3 \ft Personally I have a hard time with this one. But it may have more to do with social level and prestige within the congregation than with personal qualities and abilities.\f*  
\v 4 \w Let|strong="G2532"\w* \w each|strong="G1538"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G1438"\w* \w look|strong="G4648"\w* \w out|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w only|strong="G2532"\w* \w for|strong="G2532"\w* \w his|strong="G1438"\w* \w own|strong="G1438"\w* concerns, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w for|strong="G2532"\w* \w what|strong="G3588"\w* concerns \w others|strong="G2087"\w*.\f + \fr 2:4 \ft \+it Agape\+it* love is the opposite of selfishness.\f*   
\p
\v 5 \w In|strong="G1722"\w* \w fact|strong="G3778"\w*, \w let|strong="G2532"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* mindset \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w was|strong="G2424"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*,  
\v 6 \w who|strong="G3739"\w*, existing \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*'s \w form|strong="G3444"\w*, \w did|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w consider|strong="G2233"\w* \w equality|strong="G2470"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w a|strong="G1722"\w* \w thing|strong="G3739"\w* \w to|strong="G1722"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* grasped,\f + \fr 2:6 \ft Since Jehovah the Son was (and is) equally God, the point appears to be that He did not insist on hanging on to His prerogatives.\f*  
\v 7 \w but|strong="G2532"\w* divested \w Himself|strong="G1438"\w*, \w taking|strong="G2983"\w* \w a|strong="G1096"\w* \w slave|strong="G1401"\w*'s \w form|strong="G3444"\w*, \w coming|strong="G1096"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1096"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w likeness|strong="G3667"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w men|strong="G1401"\w*.\f + \fr 2:7 \ft Note that to be a human being is to be a slave. We are born slaves, live slaves and die slaves. We are born slaves to self, sin and death (with Satan behind the scenes); Christ offers us the option of being slaves to God, good and life. You can't stop being a slave, but you can choose your owner.\f*  
\v 8 \w And|strong="G1161"\w* \w being|strong="G1096"\w* \w found|strong="G1096"\w* \w in|strong="G1096"\w* appearance \w as|strong="G1161"\w* \w a|strong="G1096"\w* man, \w He|strong="G1161"\w* \w humbled|strong="G5013"\w* \w Himself|strong="G1438"\w*, \w becoming|strong="G1096"\w* \w obedient|strong="G5255"\w* \w to|strong="G1096"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* \w point|strong="G3360"\w* \w of|strong="G4716"\w* \w death|strong="G2288"\w*\f + \fr 2:8 \ft Hebrews 5:8 says that Jehovah the Son “learned obedience by the things that He suffered”. He had never experienced anything like that before. So what happens to us if we have the same mindset?\f*—\w even|strong="G1161"\w* \w death|strong="G2288"\w* \w on|strong="G1161"\w* \w a|strong="G1096"\w* \w cross|strong="G4716"\w*!  
\v 9 \w Indeed|strong="G2532"\w*, \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w why|strong="G1352"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w highly|strong="G5251"\w* \w exalted|strong="G5251"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w gave|strong="G2532"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w above|strong="G5228"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w*,  
\v 10 \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w at|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \bd \+w Jesus|strong="G2424"\+w*\bd*\f + \fr 2:10 \ft Note that it is at the name of \+nd Jesus\+nd*, not Christ or even Jehovah, that every knee will bow. ‘Jesus’ is His human name—recall that in Revelation the slain Lamb (5:6,12; 7:14; 12:11) receives glory and praise along with the Father. You cannot kill God, so the Lamb is Jesus. Recall further that in John 5:22 Jesus affirmed that the Father had “committed all judgment” to Him, which means that it will be Jesus sitting on the “great white throne” (Revelation 20:11), not to mention a certain “winepress” (Revelation 19:15). Although at the moment I see no way of ‘closing the question’ (as we say here in Brazil), I verily suspect that the correct transliteration of ‘Jesus’ into Hebrew will prove to be יֵסוּס and not יֵשׁוּעַ.\f* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w knee|strong="G1119"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w bow|strong="G2578"\w*—\w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w heaven|strong="G2032"\w*,\f + \fr 2:10 \ft This presumably includes the angels, whether or not they have literal ‘knees’.\f* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w earth|strong="G2709"\w*\f + \fr 2:10 \ft Those actually alive on the earth when this decree is imposed; I suppose it will be during the millennial Messianic Kingdom.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w under|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w earth|strong="G2709"\w*\f + \fr 2:10 \ft Since Hades is inside the earth (Matthew 12:40, Ephesians 4:9, 1 Samuel 28:13), this will presumably include the wicked dead, as well as the demons in the Abyss (at least). Just suppose that God wanted to confine evil to this planet; the logical place for a ‘prison’ would be beneath its crust.\f*—  
\v 11 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w tongue|strong="G1100"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* acknowledge\f + \fr 2:11 \ft The verbs ‘bow’ and ‘acknowledge’ are in the subjunctive mood in the Text, so many versions render ‘should bow’ rather than “will bow”. However, the mood of the verbs is governed by the conjunction ινα, that normally takes the subjunctive; in the context the author evidently does not intend to leave any doubt about the extent of the recognition.\f* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w is|strong="G2316"\w* \nd Sovereign\nd*, \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w glory|strong="G1391"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w*.   
\s1 Act like children of God  
\p
\v 12 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w then|strong="G2532"\w*, \w my|strong="G1722"\w* dear ones, \w just|strong="G2531"\w* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w you|strong="G1722"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w always|strong="G3842"\w* \w obeyed|strong="G5219"\w* (\w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w only|strong="G3440"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w presence|strong="G3952"\w* \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w now|strong="G3568"\w* \w much|strong="G4183"\w* \w more|strong="G3123"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* absence), \w keep|strong="G3361"\w* \w working|strong="G2716"\w* \w out|strong="G2532"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w own|strong="G1438"\w* \w salvation|strong="G4991"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w fear|strong="G5401"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w trembling|strong="G5156"\w*,  
\v 13 \w because|strong="G1063"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* Himself \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w One|strong="G3588"\w* \w at|strong="G1722"\w* \w work|strong="G1754"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*, \w both|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2309"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* produce,\f + \fr 2:13 \ft Paul places our responsibility and God's sovereignty side by side; we must consciously cooperate with Him.\f* \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \it His\it* \w good|strong="G2107"\w* \w pleasure|strong="G2107"\w*.   
\p
\v 14 \w Do|strong="G4160"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w things|strong="G3956"\w* \w without|strong="G5565"\w* \w grumbling|strong="G1112"\w* \w or|strong="G2532"\w* \w arguing|strong="G1261"\w*,\f + \fr 2:14 \ft When we grumble or argue we are rejecting the Holy Spirit's control, and the result is not purity.\f*  
\v 15 \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w you|strong="G3739"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w become|strong="G1096"\w* blameless \w and|strong="G2532"\w* pure, \w children|strong="G5043"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w without|strong="G2532"\w* fault \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w midst|strong="G3319"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w a|strong="G1096"\w* \w crooked|strong="G4646"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* depraved \w generation|strong="G1074"\w*,\f + \fr 2:15 \ft Can there be any doubt that our generation is crooked and depraved? And it is not getting any better.\f* \w among|strong="G1722"\w* \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w you|strong="G3739"\w* \w shine|strong="G5316"\w* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w light|strong="G5458"\w* bearers \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*,\f + \fr 2:15 \ft As we both live out and actively promote biblical values, the “Word of Life”, we will stand out like a bright torch at night. The darker it is, the farther any light can be seen.\f*  
\v 16 \w holding|strong="G1907"\w* \w fast|strong="G1907"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w Word|strong="G3056"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w Life|strong="G2222"\w*, \w so|strong="G1519"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w may|strong="G5547"\w* \w rejoice|strong="G2745"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w day|strong="G2250"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w did|strong="G3748"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w run|strong="G5143"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w vain|strong="G2756"\w* \w nor|strong="G3761"\w* \w labor|strong="G2872"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w nothing|strong="G3756"\w*.\f + \fr 2:16 \ft At the Accounting, one measure of our success will be the extent to which others bought into our commitment.\f*  
\v 17 Yes, \w even|strong="G2532"\w* \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w am|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* libation \w being|strong="G2532"\w* \w poured|strong="G2532"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w sacrifice|strong="G2378"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w service|strong="G3009"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w*, \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w am|strong="G2532"\w* \w glad|strong="G5463"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w rejoice|strong="G5463"\w* \w with|strong="G2532"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*.  
