\p
\v 13 Brothers, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w do|strong="G1950"\w* \w not|strong="G3768"\w* \w consider|strong="G3049"\w* \w that|strong="G1161"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G1473"\w* already claimed \w it|strong="G1161"\w*, \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w this|strong="G1161"\w*: \w forgetting|strong="G1950"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* things \w behind|strong="G3694"\w* \w and|strong="G1161"\w* straining toward \w those|strong="G1161"\w* \w ahead|strong="G1715"\w*,\f + \fr 3:13 \ft When Paul (he was still Saul) met Jesus on the road to Damascus he underwent a complete change of direction.\f*  
\v 14 \w I|strong="G1161"\w* \w press|strong="G1377"\w* \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w toward|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w goal|strong="G4649"\w* \w for|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w prize|strong="G1017"\w*, \w the|strong="G1722"\w* upward \w call|strong="G2821"\w* \w from|strong="G2596"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*\f + \fr 3:14 \ft “The upward call from God”, that is the real prize; and the only reason the Father calls anyone is because of Jesus Christ.\f* \w because|strong="G1722"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*.   
\s1 Our citizenship is in Heaven  
\p
\v 15 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w then|strong="G3767"\w*, \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w us|strong="G5426"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w mature|strong="G5046"\w* \w should|strong="G5100"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* mentality, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w on|strong="G5426"\w* \w some|strong="G5100"\w* point \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w think|strong="G5426"\w* differently, \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* reveal \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w as|strong="G3745"\w* \w well|strong="G2532"\w*.\f + \fr 3:15 \ft Paul is assuming that they will be listening to the Holy Spirit.\f*  
\v 16 \w Only|strong="G4133"\w*, \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w what|strong="G3739"\w* \w we|strong="G3739"\w* \w have|strong="G3588"\w* already \w attained|strong="G5348"\w*, let \w us|strong="G1519"\w* \w walk|strong="G4748"\w* \w by|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w same|strong="G3739"\w* rule, let \w us|strong="G1519"\w* \w be|strong="G1519"\w* \w of|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w same|strong="G3739"\w* mind.\f + \fr 3:16 \ft Less than 2% of the Greek manuscripts, of objectively inferior quality, omit “let us be of the same mind” (as in NIV, NASB, LB, TEV, etc.).\f*   
\p
\v 17 Brothers, \w join|strong="G4831"\w* \w together|strong="G4831"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* imitating \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w having|strong="G2192"\w* \w us|strong="G2249"\w*\f + \fr 3:17 \ft By changing from ‘me’ to ‘us’ I suppose Paul is including Timothy.\f* \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w pattern|strong="G5179"\w* \w take|strong="G1096"\w* note \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w walk|strong="G4043"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w same|strong="G3779"\w* \w way|strong="G3779"\w*.\f + \fr 3:17 \ft I take this as a personal challenge—to be a pattern that others can use to distinguish between friends and enemies of the cross. Since the cross of Christ represents death to self, most people are not interested.\f*  
\v 18 \w Because|strong="G1063"\w* \w many|strong="G4183"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w walking|strong="G4043"\w* \w as|strong="G1161"\w* \w enemies|strong="G2190"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w cross|strong="G4716"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*—\w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w told|strong="G3004"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w often|strong="G4178"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w now|strong="G1161"\w* \w tell|strong="G3004"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w even|strong="G2532"\w* \w with|strong="G2532"\w* tears—  
\v 19 \w whose|strong="G3739"\w* \w end|strong="G5056"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* ruin, \w whose|strong="G3739"\w* \w god|strong="G2316"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* \w stomach|strong="G2836"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w whose|strong="G3739"\w* \w glory|strong="G1391"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* shame; \w their|strong="G2532"\w* \w mind|strong="G5426"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w only|strong="G2532"\w* \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w earthly|strong="G1919"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w*.\f + \fr 3:19 \ft Apparently relativistic, humanistic materialists have been around for quite a while.\f*  
\v 20 \w But|strong="G2532"\w* \w our|strong="G2424"\w* \w citizenship|strong="G4175"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Heaven|strong="G3772"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* eagerly await \it our\it* Deliverer,\f + \fr 3:20 \ft He will deliver us from this world scene, with emphasis upon the glorification of our bodies.\f* Sovereign \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*;  
\v 21 \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w transform|strong="G3345"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w body|strong="G4983"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w our|strong="G2532"\w* \w humiliation|strong="G5014"\w*\f + \fr 3:21 \ft Although, as the Psalmist says, we are “fearfully and wonderfully made” (Psalm 139:14), it is also the case that our physical bodies limit us, and not infrequently that limitation reaches the point of being humiliating. Personally, I am ready and waiting for my glorified body, but in the meantime, I am very happy to be able to contribute to Christ's Kingdom down here.\f* \w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w conformed|strong="G4832"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w body|strong="G4983"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w His|strong="G1438"\w* \w glory|strong="G1391"\w*, \w according|strong="G2596"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w working|strong="G1753"\w* \w by|strong="G2596"\w* \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w indeed|strong="G2532"\w* \w able|strong="G1410"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w subject|strong="G5293"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w things|strong="G3956"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w Himself|strong="G1438"\w*.   
\c 4  
\m
\v 1 \w So|strong="G3779"\w* \w then|strong="G2532"\w*, \w my|strong="G1722"\w* brothers, beloved \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w longed|strong="G2532"\w* \w for|strong="G1722"\w*, \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w joy|strong="G5479"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w crown|strong="G4735"\w*, \w do|strong="G2532"\w* \w stand|strong="G4739"\w* \w fast|strong="G4739"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* Sovereign \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w this|strong="G3779"\w* \w way|strong="G3779"\w*,\f + \fr 4:1 \ft “This way” presumably refers to imitating Paul.\f* dear ones.   
\ms1 Concluding considerations  
\s1 To individuals  
\p
\v 2 \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w urge|strong="G3870"\w* \w Euodia|strong="G2136"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w urge|strong="G3870"\w* \w Syntyche|strong="G4941"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w come|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* agreement \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w*.  
\v 3 \w Yes|strong="G3483"\w*, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* urge \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w too|strong="G2532"\w*, genuine \w yokefellow|strong="G4805"\w*,\f + \fr 4:3 \ft We have here a common word for ‘yokefellow’, and although the context seems to ask for a proper name we don't know of any examples elsewhere of such use. Referring back to 2:25, the description of Epaphroditus makes him a good candidate. He is carrying this letter, and being from Philippi he would be familiar with the facts in the case.\f* \w help|strong="G4815"\w* \w these|strong="G3739"\w* \w women|strong="G3062"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* labored \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Gospel|strong="G2098"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w Clement|strong="G2815"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w rest|strong="G3062"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w fellow|strong="G4904"\w* \w workers|strong="G4904"\w*, \w whose|strong="G3739"\w* \w names|strong="G3686"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Book|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w Life|strong="G2222"\w*.\f + \fr 4:3 \ft The “Book of Life” is \+nd the\+nd* place to have your name.\f*   
\s1 Filling the mind with good things  
\p
\v 4 \w Rejoice|strong="G5463"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* Sovereign \w always|strong="G3842"\w*; \w again|strong="G3825"\w* \w I|strong="G3004"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w*, \w rejoice|strong="G5463"\w*!  
